WEBVTT

00:00.674 --> 00:01.696
The Lord, we thank you.

00:01.736 --> 00:03.460
Thank you for your word.

00:03.480 --> 00:05.485
Thank you that you have made it available to us.

00:05.886 --> 00:16.711
Thank you that you do not leave us to wander around this life aimless, that you have given your word so that we might know who you are and what you have called us to, and especially how you've saved us in Christ.

00:17.733 --> 00:19.698
God, we ask that you would be with our

00:19.810 --> 00:30.164
Our smallest disciples in the nursery, Lord, we pray that their faith would grow even in these ways that maybe are unnoticeable to us, but you are doing something in their hearts.

00:30.404 --> 00:32.707
Be with them as they interact with our nursery workers.

00:33.669 --> 00:37.354
Lord, we pray that you would strengthen them to have patience, that they would have care and have love.

00:38.115 --> 00:45.104
And God, for our students downstairs, may it be a joy and a delight to meet with their classmates, to learn about you.

00:45.905 --> 00:49.330
Grow in their hearts, a desire to know you, to love you, to serve you.

00:49.666 --> 00:54.875
And God for us up here, we want to learn to live and love like Jesus as broken people saved by grace.

00:55.696 --> 01:01.025
Help us to do that and work that through us as a result of the reading and the preaching of your word.

01:01.546 --> 01:03.289
And pray these things in Jesus' name, amen.

01:05.914 --> 01:06.795
Exodus 16.

01:10.862 --> 01:15.570
The whole Israelite community set out from Elam and came to the desert of sin.

01:15.778 --> 01:22.711
which is between Elam and Sinai on the 15th day of the second month after they had come out of Egypt.

01:22.731 --> 01:25.677
In the desert the whole community grumbled against Moses and Aaron.

01:26.218 --> 01:30.286
The Israelites said to them if we had only died by the Lord's hand in Egypt.

01:30.306 --> 01:33.573
There we sat around pots of meat and ate all the food we wanted.

01:34.214 --> 01:38.482
But you have brought us out into this desert to starve this entire assembly to death.

01:39.714 --> 01:42.759
The Lord said to Moses, I'll rain down bread from heaven for you.

01:42.779 --> 01:46.344
The people are to go out each day and gather enough for that day.

01:46.404 --> 01:51.452
In this way, I will test them and see whether they will follow my instructions.

01:52.153 --> 01:54.617
On the sixth day, they are to prepare what they bring in.

01:54.677 --> 01:58.483
And that is to be twice as much as they gather on the other days.

01:59.545 --> 02:05.394
So Moses and Aaron said to all the Israelites in the evening, you will know that it was the Lord who brought you out of Egypt.

02:05.730 --> 02:10.838
And in the morning, you will see the glory of the Lord because he has heard your grumblings against him.

02:11.519 --> 02:13.663
Who are we that you should grumble against us?

02:13.903 --> 02:24.320
Moses also said, you will know that it was the Lord when he gives you meat to eat in the evening and all the bread you want in the morning because he has heard your grumbling against him.

02:24.620 --> 02:25.241
Who are we?

02:25.302 --> 02:28.246
You are not grumbly against us but against the Lord.

02:28.266 --> 02:33.074
Then Moses told Aaron, say to the entire Israelite community,

02:33.250 --> 02:36.034
come before the Lord, for He has heard your grumbling."

02:37.195 --> 02:43.143
While Aaron was speaking to the whole Israelite community, they looked toward the desert, and there was the glory of the Lord appearing in the cloud.

02:43.904 --> 02:51.214
The Lord said to Moses, I have heard the grumbling of the Israelites tell them, at twilight you will eat meat, and in the morning you will be filled with bread.

02:51.234 --> 02:54.238
Then you will know that I am the Lord your God.

02:55.360 --> 03:00.146
Well, that evening quail came, covered the camp, and in the morning there was a layer of dew around the camp.

03:00.674 --> 03:04.919
When the dew was gone, thin flakes like frost on the ground appeared on the desert floor.

03:05.620 --> 03:08.083
When the Israelites saw it, they said to each other, what is it?

03:08.624 --> 03:09.986
For they did not know what it was.

03:11.007 --> 03:14.131
Moses said to them, it is the bread the Lord has given you to eat.

03:14.692 --> 03:18.517
This is what the Lord has commanded everyone is to gather as much as they need.

03:18.537 --> 03:21.540
Take an omore for each person you have in your tent.

03:22.542 --> 03:25.906
The Israelites did as they were told, some gathered much, some little.

03:26.850 --> 03:30.595
And when they measured it by the Omer, the one who gathered much did not have too much.

03:31.016 --> 03:33.359
The one who gathered little did not have too little.

03:34.160 --> 03:35.943
Everyone had gathered just as much as they needed.

03:36.604 --> 03:39.688
And then Moses said to them, no one is to keep any of it until morning.

03:41.070 --> 03:43.714
However, some of them paid no attention to Moses.

03:43.994 --> 03:47.600
They kept part of it until morning, but it was full of maggots and began to smell.

03:48.321 --> 03:49.582
So Moses was angry with them.

03:50.524 --> 03:52.787
Each morning, everyone gathered as much as they needed.

03:52.887 --> 03:54.930
And when the sun grew hot, it melted away.

03:55.394 --> 04:02.023
On the sixth day, they gathered twice as much, two homers for each person, and the leaders of the community came and reported this to Moses.

04:02.403 --> 04:04.526
He said to them, this is what the Lord commanded.

04:04.566 --> 04:09.152
Tomorrow is to be a day of Sabbath rest, a holy Sabbath to the Lord.

04:09.193 --> 04:14.800
So bake what you want to bake, and boil what you want to boil, save whatever is left, and keep it until morning.

04:15.721 --> 04:17.924
So they saved it until morning as Moses commanded.

04:17.964 --> 04:20.568
And it did not stink, or get maggots in it.

04:21.609 --> 04:25.234
Eat it today, Moses said, because today is a Sabbath to the Lord.

04:25.506 --> 04:27.649
You will not find any of it on the ground today.

04:28.189 --> 04:32.715
Six days you are to gather it, but on the seventh day, the Sabbath there will not be any.

04:32.775 --> 04:38.642
Nevertheless, some of the people went out on the seventh day to gather it, but they found none.

04:38.682 --> 04:44.049
Then the Lord said to Moses, how long will you refuse to keep my commands and my instructions?

04:44.850 --> 04:47.032
Bear in mind that the Lord has given you the Sabbath.

04:47.493 --> 04:50.356
That is why on the sixth day he gives you bread for two days.

04:51.278 --> 04:53.620
Everyone is to stay where they are on the seventh day.

04:53.640 --> 04:54.962
No one is to go out.

04:55.746 --> 04:57.368
So the people rested on the seventh day.

04:58.749 --> 05:00.471
Now the people of Israel called the bread manna.

05:00.832 --> 05:04.996
It was white, like coriander seed and tasted like wafers made with honey.

05:06.298 --> 05:08.500
Moses said, this is what the Lord has commanded.

05:08.540 --> 05:11.824
Take an omer of manna and keep it for the generations to come.

05:12.665 --> 05:17.010
So they can see the bread I gave you to eat in the wilderness when I brought you out of Egypt.

05:17.651 --> 05:21.074
So Moses said to Aaron, take a jar and put an omer of manna in it.

05:21.235 --> 05:24.338
Then place it before the Lord to be kept for the generations to come.

05:25.026 --> 05:30.793
As the Lord commanded Moses, Aaron put the manna with the tablets of the covenant law so that it might be preserved.

05:31.214 --> 05:35.639
The Israelites ate manna 40 years until they came to a land that was settled.

05:36.100 --> 05:38.963
They ate manna until they reached the border of Canaan.

05:39.724 --> 05:43.689
This is the word of the Lord, and we say, thanks be to God.

05:43.729 --> 05:54.162
Now, who here likes tests?

05:55.106 --> 05:57.308
Who here likes tests?

05:57.328 --> 05:58.629
You remember taking tests?

05:58.970 --> 06:06.797
If you're not in school, you probably remember taking tests in the feelings that it brings up.

06:06.837 --> 06:15.366
You remember studying late night into the next day, maybe, to get ready for the test.

06:16.326 --> 06:24.114
You remember the pressure that you felt on exam day, the anxiety as you were taking the test,

06:24.194 --> 06:32.085
And then really the anxiety that builds until you get your score back to where you're either relieved or you're disappointed.

06:33.486 --> 06:34.568
How about driving tests?

06:35.028 --> 06:35.749
Driving tests.

06:35.829 --> 06:51.250
You remember driving tests where you have your instructor, your stoic instructor sitting in the seat next to you with clipboard in hand ready to make comments on your ability to drive and to adhere to the laws of the land.

06:52.578 --> 06:54.981
and you are sitting in the next seat over, you are rigid.

06:55.342 --> 06:59.007
You have your hands firmly fixed on 10 and two.

06:59.647 --> 07:05.715
Test, we don't really like to be tested, but it is a useful thing.

07:07.298 --> 07:10.862
Well, God tests Israel in the wilderness.

07:11.884 --> 07:16.690
We read that he tests them so that he might know if they will respond

07:16.770 --> 07:17.811
to his instruction.

07:18.232 --> 07:21.857
Oh, God has freed the Israelites from slavery in Egypt.

07:22.138 --> 07:26.804
And now he wants to know that do these people, do they know me?

07:27.325 --> 07:29.268
Will these people follow me?

07:29.768 --> 07:31.431
Will these people trust me?

07:32.793 --> 07:35.216
So God tests them.

07:35.837 --> 07:41.785
And in Deuteronomy chapter eight as Moses, that gives kind of an interpretation of the wilderness journey.

07:42.146 --> 07:45.170
He says that the Lord has caused you to hunger.

07:45.538 --> 07:50.664
The Lord cause you to hunger in the wilderness so that he might know what is in your heart.

07:50.704 --> 07:52.186
Will you trust him or not?

07:53.107 --> 07:56.591
And so we see here that the Lord tests his people.

07:57.131 --> 07:59.354
He brings them to this place of hunger.

08:00.255 --> 08:04.219
So they will know, he will know what they are about, where they are at.

08:04.279 --> 08:11.467
And this first test he says to them, I want you to go out and I want you to gather manna daily.

08:11.507 --> 08:13.810
I don't want you.

08:14.114 --> 08:15.436
to keep it until the morning.

08:15.597 --> 08:17.340
I want you to pick it up every morning.

08:18.121 --> 08:18.862
Don't keep it though.

08:19.022 --> 08:19.964
Don't keep it overnight.

08:20.745 --> 08:21.266
And what do they do?

08:21.306 --> 08:23.270
They keep it overnight.

08:23.691 --> 08:24.332
Why?

08:24.372 --> 08:25.093
Why do they do this?

08:25.153 --> 08:28.078
Because they do not trust in the Lord's provision.

08:28.459 --> 08:35.271
The Lord tests them and what they see, what we see is that Israel does not fare very well in their tests.

08:35.291 --> 08:37.234
They do not trust the Lord to provide.

08:37.698 --> 08:38.839
They're hungry in the wilderness.

08:38.859 --> 08:43.265
They're coming out of a place of Egypt where their food was probably rationed and monitored.

08:43.285 --> 08:48.371
So it's not like they had full bellies, but now they wake up this morning and they see this.

08:48.391 --> 08:52.175
This wafer-like substance, this wafer bread on the ground, sweet to the taste.

08:52.435 --> 08:54.137
They eat and they have their fill.

08:54.438 --> 08:58.462
It probably feels really good and they don't want to let this provision pass.

08:58.503 --> 08:59.924
They don't want to let this go.

08:59.964 --> 09:04.850
They don't trust that the Lord will continue to provide that the next morning they'll wake up

09:05.218 --> 09:08.801
And although all of the resources are gone, they don't trust that it's going to be there again.

09:09.602 --> 09:11.684
They fail to trust in the Lord's daily provision.

09:12.605 --> 09:15.348
What in the Lord says, well, I'm going to give this to you.

09:15.588 --> 09:20.212
Six days, six out of every seven days, I want you to go out and gather on the seventh day.

09:20.232 --> 09:21.594
I don't want you to gather.

09:21.614 --> 09:23.395
I want you to stay, stay inside.

09:23.415 --> 09:24.376
You don't have to go out.

09:24.637 --> 09:30.282
I'm gonna provide for you enough on the sixth, so away on the seventh, you can just kind of chill into rest.

09:30.382 --> 09:31.283
I want you to rest.

09:31.844 --> 09:32.384
What do they do?

09:32.424 --> 09:34.386
Nevertheless,

09:34.498 --> 09:38.504
Some of the people went out and gathered on the morning of the seventh day.

09:38.564 --> 09:40.627
Why do they do this?

09:42.189 --> 09:52.824
They're coming out of a place of slavery where they were servants to Pharaoh and to the most powerful empire in the known world.

09:53.505 --> 09:59.794
And surely this God who has exhibited his might and his strength over Egypt, well surely he is a God like them.

09:59.906 --> 10:05.073
where he wants them to be working consistently and constantly working seven days a week.

10:05.574 --> 10:11.401
They don't trust that this God is a compassionate God, that this is a God who wants to grant them rest.

10:13.023 --> 10:16.448
And so they go out and they gather, they find that it's not there.

10:16.488 --> 10:22.857
They don't trust the Lord to provide, they don't trust the Lord to grant them rest.

10:24.819 --> 10:26.962
Now as we talk about

10:27.138 --> 10:31.983
testing as we look at testing through the lens of our own lives.

10:32.464 --> 10:34.446
There are a couple of things that we need to say.

10:34.506 --> 10:42.455
First, we need to admit, say it out loud, that God does test his people.

10:43.356 --> 10:45.719
I know this is uncomfortable, it's uncomfortable for me.

10:46.079 --> 10:48.141
Maybe it's uncomfortable for you that God does test his people.

10:48.161 --> 10:52.306
We have evidence throughout Scripture that God tests his people.

10:53.026 --> 10:58.014
So we have this passage, but just before this passage, we looked at Exodus 15.

10:58.054 --> 11:02.781
We didn't talk about it last week, but God, he allows his people to grow thirsty.

11:03.182 --> 11:05.686
He wants to test them to see if they will follow his instruction.

11:06.667 --> 11:09.692
And we have in Genesis chapter 22, is that remember, Genesis 22?

11:09.752 --> 11:11.394
Abraham?

11:12.156 --> 11:21.490
Abraham, Genesis 22.1, God tests Abraham to see if he will give up his only, his one and only son Isaac, the son that he loves.

11:22.050 --> 11:29.318
Judges chapter three, God allows Israel's enemies to remain kind of in the land that is surrounding them.

11:30.059 --> 11:30.380
Why?

11:30.480 --> 11:37.107
So that God can test whether or not the God's people will follow his instructions and his commands.

11:38.269 --> 11:41.232
John chapter six, Jesus tests his disciples.

11:41.933 --> 11:46.578
There is a crowd of thousands of people that are coming to see Jesus.

11:46.658 --> 11:52.206
Jesus turns to his disciples specifically, Philip, and he says, where shall we get bread to feed all of these people?

11:53.248 --> 11:56.252
Philip says, oh, we're not concerned with Philip.

11:56.272 --> 12:05.967
But then the commentator, John, John says, Jesus said this to test him, because he already knew in his mind what he was going to do.

12:07.610 --> 12:11.015
Yes, it is true that God does test his people.

12:13.478 --> 12:15.922
But we have to put up some boundaries.

12:16.450 --> 12:17.772
We have to put up some boundaries.

12:18.233 --> 12:30.056
In the book of James, James says, when you go through times of temptation, when you go through times of trial, do not say that the Lord is tempting you.

12:31.057 --> 12:35.666
Because God himself cannot be tempted and he does not tempt anybody.

12:38.562 --> 12:42.053
Yes, God does lead us into times of testing.

12:42.374 --> 12:46.307
He either ordains it himself or he permits it.

12:46.588 --> 12:52.146
He permits it to happen, but God himself is not responsible for leading us to sin.

12:54.210 --> 12:57.413
When we sin, James says, when we sin, this is our own doing.

12:57.433 --> 13:00.376
This is a result of us following our own desires.

13:00.637 --> 13:10.367
This is kind of what we see happening in the Garden of Eden when God has Adam and Eve there, and he says, hey, here's a beautiful forest, beautiful provision for you in this garden.

13:10.707 --> 13:13.970
You can have any fruit from any tree in the garden except for that one.

13:13.990 --> 13:15.372
Just don't eat that one.

13:16.033 --> 13:18.035
The choice really is yours to make.

13:18.075 --> 13:21.298
You can listen to me, the creator, or you can

13:21.634 --> 13:25.560
do what you want to in your own heart.

13:25.660 --> 13:28.124
And they end up listening to the created.

13:28.224 --> 13:32.651
They listen to the creature, the one that they're supposed to be ruling over.

13:32.931 --> 13:34.514
That really God gives them a choice.

13:34.574 --> 13:43.788
This is a faith test to see if they will follow God, follow the way of life, or if they will follow the way that leads to death.

13:44.729 --> 13:45.330
A choice.

13:46.018 --> 13:49.343
When we are tested, we have choices that we make.

13:49.363 --> 13:52.849
So that good question to ask is how are we doing in the tests?

13:52.869 --> 13:56.174
How are we doing in the trials that we are facing in life?

13:57.877 --> 14:06.591
Maybe the Lord has permitted a financial hardship for you right now, or maybe the Lord has permitted financial abundance.

14:07.853 --> 14:10.738
And in this time, we are tested.

14:10.914 --> 14:14.340
And we find that, oh, what do we do with these resources?

14:14.400 --> 14:26.341
We want to hoard them either because we don't have enough, or we want to hoard them because we have too much, and we don't trust that the Lord will provide for us daily, kind of like the Israelites.

14:27.463 --> 14:35.698
And instead of giving generously the being a stewards, a good stewards of our finances, we take it for ourselves.

14:36.482 --> 14:42.330
Or maybe the Lord has permitted a time of sickness for you or for a loved one.

14:43.071 --> 14:49.480
And this time of testing, you are turning your heart away from the Lord.

14:49.560 --> 14:51.082
Your questioning is goodness to you.

14:51.122 --> 14:55.028
Your questioning is love for you and his provision for you.

14:55.989 --> 15:00.996
Living in our society, we're constantly confronted with these tests.

15:01.136 --> 15:02.578
How do we use our time?

15:03.394 --> 15:08.621
There's so many offerings to us, to our kids, the sports and activities.

15:10.063 --> 15:19.555
How are we giving ourselves the necessary time to come away from these, to rest, to find refreshment, and to worship the Lord?

15:20.296 --> 15:30.770
Are we allowing ourselves to come away so that we can love our neighbor as we're called, so that we can go to those who are lonely?

15:31.010 --> 15:33.214
maybe failing to take this time away.

15:33.274 --> 15:45.275
We are failing to give the Lord our worship, failing to trust that He will uphold all of our cares and concerns that He will do the necessary work while we withdraw and rest.

15:45.596 --> 15:48.942
How are we doing in these times?

15:49.142 --> 15:55.954
In these times where we have these choices to make, that we don't like to be

15:56.194 --> 15:58.697
It's not comfortable.

15:59.017 --> 16:03.283
We actually arrange our lives so that we will mitigate hardships.

16:05.425 --> 16:07.968
But this is how God works.

16:08.228 --> 16:10.691
God tests His people.

16:11.492 --> 16:15.237
Now God doesn't test His people because He doesn't know what's in their heart already.

16:15.257 --> 16:18.020
God knows everything about us, past, present and future.

16:18.741 --> 16:26.130
God gives us tests or God ordains, permits tests to happen, however you want to say it.

16:26.498 --> 16:31.263
so that we will know the content of our hearts, so that we will know where we're at with Him.

16:31.303 --> 16:34.486
And the early, these are opportunities for us to grow.

16:34.527 --> 16:39.612
Testing and going through trials become opportunities for us to mature in our faith.

16:39.992 --> 16:46.499
It tells us where we're at, where our hearts are at with the Lord, and it gives us a chance to grow in our faith as we depend on Him.

16:47.881 --> 16:52.946
Now, in 2014, Christy and I, we lived in Seattle at the time.

16:53.090 --> 16:57.524
And I was on the campus of Seattle Pacific University.

16:57.604 --> 16:59.128
I was studying in their library.

16:59.811 --> 17:07.474
And in 2014, on this particular morning afternoon when I was studying in the library, there was a shooting on campus.

17:08.162 --> 17:13.349
So there was somebody who came into the student center and opened fire on a group of people.

17:13.830 --> 17:19.799
And so I'm sitting there in the library and some of the workers are coming around telling people that there's an active shooter on campus.

17:20.019 --> 17:22.162
We don't know if this is a smaller campus.

17:22.182 --> 17:23.764
We don't know where the shooter is.

17:24.506 --> 17:28.411
But we need you to come and we're going to go into lockdown.

17:30.014 --> 17:35.922
And so this is kind of a revelation of where is my, how do I respond in this?

17:36.162 --> 17:37.964
I've never been in this situation before.

17:38.525 --> 17:47.077
I've seen a lot of shows where these really brave and courageous people, they seek out maybe somebody that's trying to inflict harm and they try to wrestle them down.

17:47.137 --> 17:52.164
Or maybe they seek out people that are maybe in harm's way or in exposed areas.

17:52.204 --> 17:57.351
They put themselves in danger's way so that they can help other people out.

17:57.371 --> 17:59.474
I've never been in this situation before.

18:00.034 --> 18:06.421
My response was, I went into this dark conference room with the rest of everybody from the library.

18:06.941 --> 18:14.490
They turned off the lights, they closed the doors, our hearts were racing fast, and we held our breath every time the door opened, because we didn't know what's gonna happen.

18:15.310 --> 18:16.892
Test reveal.

18:17.593 --> 18:21.097
Test reveal where our hearts are at.

18:21.117 --> 18:24.480
I wouldn't have known how it would have responded had I not been in that situation.

18:25.962 --> 18:27.684
Now Israel, God tests Israel.

18:28.345 --> 18:29.746
So if they may know

18:30.434 --> 18:33.618
their hearts, where their hearts are at, but also so that they will grow.

18:33.638 --> 18:35.201
These are God's people.

18:35.281 --> 18:39.687
He says, I want them to know that I am the Lord their God.

18:40.668 --> 18:41.509
I am their God.

18:42.331 --> 18:43.492
I am a God for them.

18:43.532 --> 18:44.594
They are my people.

18:44.714 --> 18:45.876
I want them to learn this.

18:46.717 --> 18:50.061
So what does this time of testing reveal about the Lord?

18:50.602 --> 18:56.210
Well, first it reveals that the Lord is all an all-powerful and intimate provider.

18:57.762 --> 19:00.587
God is an all-powerful and intimate provider.

19:01.108 --> 19:03.232
Now, we said that they don't trust Him.

19:03.312 --> 19:05.536
They don't trust Him to daily provide.

19:05.556 --> 19:13.249
Now, why doesn't God just heap like tons and tons of grain on these carts and send them with the Israelites?

19:13.269 --> 19:20.722
Why doesn't God send just like cattle, just multitude of cattle to journey with the Israelites and say, hey,

19:21.090 --> 19:28.741
Yeah, you guys are taking care of this, I'll ask you about five, 10 years, I gotta go off and I gotta do some other work, but you guys will be okay, you'll have enough food.

19:29.502 --> 19:34.229
Once that God provides daily, daily He provides this manna.

19:35.010 --> 19:35.291
Why?

19:35.311 --> 19:37.614
To show them that He is there with them.

19:38.295 --> 19:44.404
That step by step He is there, that through the hardship He will provide for them, that He is in control of all nature.

19:45.105 --> 19:48.370
And that He's not just gonna provide, He is going to provide an abundance.

19:49.250 --> 19:53.816
Israel learns that through this daily provision of manner, they can trust him.

19:54.857 --> 19:56.499
They can trust him with their daily need.

19:57.701 --> 20:09.596
Oh, he also learned that this God really does desire rest for them, that this is a God who is compassionate, that this is a God who cares not just about their physical well-being, but really their spiritual, their soul.

20:09.656 --> 20:17.426
Now they're coming out of a place of slavery with a king who probably worked them seven days a week back breaking labor.

20:18.274 --> 20:19.695
They work to stay alive.

20:20.356 --> 20:21.677
They work to stay safe.

20:23.119 --> 20:27.863
But now they're finding out that, no, this God really is serious.

20:28.063 --> 20:30.806
He will give us what we need if we withdraw.

20:31.166 --> 20:34.129
And if we rest, God will continue to uphold the universe.

20:34.189 --> 20:37.112
God will provide for us body and soul.

20:37.492 --> 20:38.953
He will give us what is needed.

20:40.755 --> 20:41.656
It's not comfortable.

20:42.877 --> 20:48.082
It's not something that the Israelites probably would choose for themselves, but God grows them.

20:48.674 --> 20:57.023
God, well, we'd like to think that God grows them, that their hearts are changed in this time of testing as it reveals to them who He is.

20:59.005 --> 21:03.150
Well, because this is how God continues to work in our lives.

21:04.752 --> 21:06.514
God gives us tests.

21:06.854 --> 21:14.162
God permits trials in our lives so that we might know Him, so that we might love Him.

21:14.434 --> 21:20.040
so that we might grow into maturity as his people and find what we need in him.

21:20.060 --> 21:29.631
Now, if you think about it, you're probably not gonna choose, make these decisions for yourself, right?

21:29.651 --> 21:31.613
You're not gonna choose to go through trials.

21:32.194 --> 21:40.262
If I was in control of my life, I feel like my job is to avoid trials and to avoid hardships, but then we're not going to grow.

21:40.282 --> 21:43.506
Think about, does anybody lift weights?

21:44.706 --> 21:46.773
Does anybody try to build muscle, right?

21:47.435 --> 21:48.378
It works, right?

21:48.418 --> 21:52.070
It works to build muscle if you go to the gym and just talk a lot to people.

21:53.073 --> 21:58.450
It works if you go to the gym, if you read a book, if you read a book about lifting weights, yeah.

21:58.722 --> 22:01.124
No, no, that's not how it works at all.

22:01.485 --> 22:04.448
In order to build muscle, you have to stress the muscle, right?

22:04.768 --> 22:06.029
You have to increase your weight.

22:06.049 --> 22:08.331
You have to increase your repetitions.

22:08.371 --> 22:10.954
What you're doing is you're actually breaking down your muscle.

22:10.974 --> 22:17.520
You're creating microscopic tears in the muscle fiber in your body because God created us to be so amazing.

22:18.301 --> 22:21.685
Your body actually rebuilds that muscle and makes it stronger.

22:21.725 --> 22:27.250
Think about our faith life in this same way.

22:28.066 --> 22:30.369
as we think about discipleship.

22:31.030 --> 22:38.320
As we think about discipleship as a process or as a journey where we are wanting to grow in our trust of the Lord.

22:38.361 --> 22:43.708
We are, as we continue on this journey, as we think about discipleship through stages.

22:44.209 --> 22:53.141
And each stage we come to a deeper place of trust in the Lord, where we are more willing to give ourselves, more of ourselves to the Lord.

22:54.884 --> 22:56.466
I think about it in this sense.

22:56.802 --> 22:58.624
And this is where growth comes through.

22:59.646 --> 23:00.687
There's a place.

23:01.949 --> 23:03.491
There's a place in these stages.

23:04.312 --> 23:05.353
It's called the wall.

23:05.614 --> 23:12.162
Janet Hagberg and Robert Gulick wrote a book, The Critical Journey, where they talk about the discipleship journey.

23:12.182 --> 23:15.126
It's called The Critical Journey, but the stages of discipleship.

23:15.146 --> 23:24.178
And there is something that they call the wall, this place we come into, this place where our will comes face to face or head to head with God's will.

23:24.610 --> 23:25.732
It's a time of crisis.

23:26.212 --> 23:28.135
It's a season of challenge.

23:28.155 --> 23:40.512
It's a time when we are led to where we have no more resources, where we cannot depend on ourselves any longer, or if we want to continue to grow in our faith and in our trust, we have to turn to the Lord.

23:40.732 --> 23:41.793
We can't go around the wall.

23:41.813 --> 23:42.454
We can't go over.

23:42.494 --> 23:43.336
We can't dig under it.

23:43.536 --> 23:46.320
We have to go through the hard, difficult place of it.

23:46.720 --> 23:48.082
This is the wall.

23:49.058 --> 23:56.610
But as you look back, as you make it through the wall, as you go through the difficulties that you realize that this is where you've experienced the most growth.

23:57.691 --> 24:02.258
Think about the times in your life where you've seen the most maturing as you look back.

24:02.379 --> 24:05.143
Probably not in the midst of it, you don't think, oh, I'm really getting mature here.

24:05.524 --> 24:07.887
You probably think, oh, this is really hard.

24:08.909 --> 24:12.915
It's the times when you were most probably put under stress and put under pressure.

24:13.195 --> 24:14.898
Not the times you were the most comfortable.

24:15.490 --> 24:20.681
I think about for myself when I was in undergrad back at Western Michigan University.

24:21.322 --> 24:24.910
I would play soccer at five to six nights a week down the rec center.

24:25.070 --> 24:26.754
This is what I love to do.

24:26.834 --> 24:27.756
This was my life.

24:29.099 --> 24:32.626
But because of an experience where I was sledding,

24:32.706 --> 24:35.028
I was sledding in a place I was not supposed to be sledding.

24:35.889 --> 24:37.130
I broke my collarbone.

24:37.671 --> 24:38.932
And so I was out.

24:39.032 --> 24:40.013
It was a very painful thing.

24:40.033 --> 24:41.415
I was out for a couple months.

24:42.055 --> 24:46.660
It was during these couple months where I wasn't able to play soccer, like I love doing.

24:46.940 --> 24:50.564
The Lord kind of brought me into this place where He deepened.

24:50.724 --> 24:51.805
He deepened my trust.

24:51.825 --> 24:52.866
He deepened my faith.

24:53.246 --> 25:01.074
And Him, He connected me with a local campus ministry, a body that I never would have gone to had I still been engaged in those rec league

25:01.154 --> 25:02.456
likely soccer nights.

25:02.877 --> 25:18.422
You talk to some of the senior members of our congregation, those who have been through it, through illness, through accident, through loss, through job insecurity, through political instability, through broken relationships, talk to them.

25:19.143 --> 25:21.567
They will tell you that yes, it is hard.

25:21.968 --> 25:28.178
No, it is not something that I would have chosen for myself, but yes, this is a place where God has used to grow me.

25:28.514 --> 25:36.705
I can tell for certain that God has taken this situation, he has made it for my good, or I depend on him, where my faith is matured, and I trust him.

25:38.708 --> 25:40.149
God is our God.

25:40.610 --> 25:42.513
He has claimed us for his own.

25:42.993 --> 25:48.881
He loves us as his children, and so he tests us to reveal where we're at with him, where our trust is at.

25:48.901 --> 25:55.570
So he gives us opportunities to grow in our faith with him.

25:55.874 --> 26:02.046
bringing this to a close by talking about that thing that we all fear when we talk about tests.

26:03.269 --> 26:04.351
What if I fail?

26:05.894 --> 26:07.597
What if I fail the test?

26:08.780 --> 26:11.385
What if I don't get that mark that I was hoping for?

26:12.767 --> 26:13.950
What if I don't get that grade?

26:13.970 --> 26:16.114
What if I don't measure up?

26:17.954 --> 26:26.609
What if in my individual life, or what if we as a church, as we journey into this new season, this new mission, this new vision, what happens if we fail?

26:28.573 --> 26:29.474
We probably will.

26:30.717 --> 26:32.780
There will probably be times when we do fail.

26:33.862 --> 26:42.738
The Israelites, they journeyed hundreds and hundreds of years with God, and I don't know if they ever really truly came to a place of deep trust in the Lord.

26:45.538 --> 26:52.266
There are gonna be times when we fail to respond in our faith the way that we want to.

26:52.306 --> 26:54.889
We want to live a life of deep faith.

26:54.909 --> 26:59.274
We want to honor the Lord through our perseverance, through turning to Him time and again.

26:59.334 --> 27:05.501
But we are not straight A students when it comes to this faith life journey.

27:07.163 --> 27:09.646
We go through hardship and we complain.

27:10.407 --> 27:13.010
We go through hardship and we are impatient.

27:13.922 --> 27:19.189
We go through hardship and we turn away from the Lord.

27:19.209 --> 27:23.715
We go through hardship and we look to alternative places for comfort.

27:23.775 --> 27:27.560
We go through hardship and we fail to follow the Lord's leading.

27:27.600 --> 27:30.244
We fail to take action where God is calling us to go.

27:30.284 --> 27:33.168
We are broken people.

27:33.408 --> 27:38.535
We are broken people saved by grace on this journey of trying to learn and live like Jesus.

27:40.077 --> 27:40.818
But thankfully,

27:41.698 --> 27:44.983
Thankfully, we have a savior who himself has been tested.

27:46.065 --> 27:57.163
We have a savior who has been through every trial and temptation as we have, and yet he did not sin, says the author of Hebrews chapter four.

27:58.004 --> 28:08.882
But Jesus Christ, God, who is also one of us, he went through the worst test that any human being has ever had to go through, rejection by his friends.

28:09.474 --> 28:18.089
separation from God, the intimacy of God, being mocked by the people, being beaten, and eventually hung up on a cross.

28:18.870 --> 28:25.161
But Jesus Christ was so concerned he was so honed in on the Father's will that he continued with it.

28:25.581 --> 28:28.646
He endured that pain and that punishment and that separation.

28:29.167 --> 28:35.538
And what we find is that through the greatest test that has ever been given to any human, Jesus Christ withstood it.

28:35.874 --> 28:43.343
Jesus Christ was obedient to the Father, and what he did was he took our sins, our failings, upon himself at the cross.

28:44.184 --> 28:49.070
And now the greatest triumph, the greatest victory has occurred through this greatest testing.

28:49.991 --> 29:01.665
Because now, as we walk through life and as we go through tests and as we fail, we know that God does not regard us in the same way that God, instead of looking at us, he looks to Jesus Christ.

29:02.246 --> 29:05.650
The perfect score of Jesus has been given to us.

29:06.338 --> 29:07.520
And now we can be sure.

29:07.901 --> 29:25.953
We can be absolutely confident that as we go through life, as we go through these trials, we can be certain that God is with us, that this intimate, all-powerful God, He is right there journeying with us because He loves us as His children, because He cares for us.

29:26.434 --> 29:27.636
He is not going to let us go.

29:27.656 --> 29:30.802
He's going to give us exactly what we need when we need it.

29:31.970 --> 29:38.139
We can trust this because Jesus Christ has given up his life for us and he has raised from the dead for our life.

29:39.321 --> 29:41.625
God gives us tests, it's not comfortable.

29:42.486 --> 29:46.793
God gives us tests so we might know what's inside of us.

29:47.634 --> 29:54.765
So we might know that we can trust him and so that we might grow in this beautiful faith that he's given to us.

29:55.666 --> 29:58.130
All of God's people said, amen.

30:05.122 --> 30:10.230
All right, our response, Psalm 116, what shall I repay to the Lord for His goodness to me?

30:10.270 --> 30:12.473
Think about your life.

30:13.355 --> 30:15.598
Are you going through any trials, any tests right now?

30:17.701 --> 30:18.623
And how are you responding?

30:18.783 --> 30:21.107
Are you responding in bitterness, complaint?

30:21.988 --> 30:24.251
Are you seeking sources of outside comfort?

30:26.154 --> 30:29.860
Do you need to offer to the Lord God, strengthen my faith and help me to turn to you?

30:31.563 --> 30:33.746
Are you struggling to trust the Lord for daily provision?

30:34.466 --> 30:37.651
Are you taking for reserve more than you need?

30:38.052 --> 30:39.895
Are you basing your security off of it?

30:41.458 --> 30:44.583
Are you neglecting to take rest offered by the Lord?

30:45.124 --> 30:52.356
Are you failing to trust in His provision, trust that He's going to uphold things while you step away and seek Him out in worship?

30:54.119 --> 31:00.530
Or do you need to cast yourself upon Christ who has already passed every test for us?

